AN ACT relating to the management of land; requiring the Sagebrush Ecosystem
Council in the State Department of Conservation and Natural
Resources to establish by regulation a program to mitigate damage to
sagebrush ecosystems; requiring the Council to [set forth in regulation
any method or formula used by the habitat quantification tool
developed by the Council as part of the program;] adopt certain
regulations related to the program; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Sagebrush Ecosystem Council within the State Department of
2 Conservation and Natural Resources. Existing law requires the Council to establish a program
3 to mitigate damage to sagebrush ecosystems by creating a system to award credits to certain
4 persons and entities to protect, enhance or restore sagebrush ecosystems. (NRS 232.162) This
5 bill requires the Council to establish the program by regulation. In establishing the program,
6 this bill further requires the Council to [: (1) develop a habitat quantification tool; and (2)] set
7 forth in regulation [any method or formula used by the habitat quantification tool for
8 calculating debits and credits.] : (1) the process to apply to participate in the program; (2)
9 the process for the review of an application by the Council; (3) the process by which an
10 applicant may appeal any decision of the Council relating to the application; and (4) the
11 process by which the Council will periodically review any activity or project that has
12 been approved by the Council to create credits or acquire debits pursuant to the
13 program.
